# Matplotlib is a comprehensive library for creating static, animated, and interactive visualizations in Python.
# Use Matplotlib when you need full control over every aspect of your plot or when creating complex, custom visualizations that are not directly supported by higher-level libraries.

# Seaborn is a Python data visualization library based on matplotlib. It provides a high-level interface for drawing attractive and informative statistical graphics.
# Use Seaborn for exploratory data analysis and when you want to create statistical plots easily and quickly.